your wind and fire rings.

36:43.201 --> 36:44.703
Rebel, how did it go for you?

36:44.703 --> 36:46.329
- It wasn't like
any weapon I've made before.

36:46.329 --> 36:48.289
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:48.289 --> 36:50.625
<i>Where I had to build them</i>
<i>off of many little pieces</i>

36:50.625 --> 36:53.962
<i>riveted together with,</i>
<i>like, 1/4-inch steel.</i>

36:53.962 --> 36:55.880
- Chuck, how'd it go for you?

36:55.880 --> 36:58.591
- It was, uh,
definitely a challenge.

36:58.591 --> 37:01.469
<i>Had to re-arrange my forge</i>
<i>to fit everything</i>

37:01.469 --> 37:03.680
<i>but it's forged 5160</i>

37:03.680 --> 37:05.473
<i>and then parts</i>
<i>are all made individually</i>

37:05.473 --> 37:07.934
<i>and welded together</i>
<i>before heat treat.</i>

37:07.934 --> 37:10.061
- All right, gentlemen,
each of your weapons

37:10.061 --> 37:12.981
will now be put through
a series of three tests.

37:12.981 --> 37:15.692
There will be a strength test,
a sharpness test,

37:15.692 --> 37:18.153
and, up first, the kill test.

37:18.153 --> 37:19.821
Doug.

37:19.821 --> 37:22.741
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:22.741 --> 37:25.201
- Bladesmiths, to find out
what kind of lethal damage

37:25.201 --> 37:27.412
your weapon will do,
I will take your rings

37:27.412 --> 37:29.748
and deliver slashes and thrusts
on this pig carcass.

37:29.748 --> 37:31.249
Rebel, you're up first.
You ready?

37:31.249 --> 37:33.209
- More than ready.
- Let's do this.

37:33.209 --> 37:35.503
<i>- The amount of stress</i>
<i>from him hitting that pig,</i>

37:35.503 --> 37:37.922
I'm afraid the rivets
may try to come loose.

37:37.922 --> 37:40.592
<i>[tense rising tone]</i>

37:40.592 --> 37:43.470
<i>[heavy metal music]</i>

37:43.470 --> 37:50.477
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:52.312 --> 37:53.772
Dang.

37:53.772 --> 38:00.862
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:02.238 --> 38:03.865
- Nice job.

38:03.865 --> 38:07.118
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:07.118 --> 38:08.953
- All right.

38:08.953 --> 38:10.830
I like the construction here.
It's unique.

38:10.830 --> 38:12.373
I've never seen this
done before.

38:12.373 --> 38:13.958
It makes it very sturdy

38:13.958 --> 38:16.544
but it adds
a little more weight to it.

38:16.544 --> 38:19.631
It makes siding it
a little bit more difficult,

38:19.631 --> 38:23.468
but yet, once you get going
your wind and fire will kill.

38:23.468 --> 38:25.553
- Thank you.
- Good job.

38:25.553 --> 38:27.096
All right, Chuck, your turn.
You ready?

38:27.096 --> 38:29.182
- I'm ready.

38:29.182 --> 38:31.935
For me, the big concern
is the welds.

38:31.935 --> 38:33.645
That's the weak point.

38:33.645 --> 38:40.443
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:45.490 --> 38:47.784
- It ain't critical.

38:47.784 --> 38:49.494
<i>- Just like that one broke,</i>

38:49.494 --> 38:51.913
<i>any of the other ones</i>
<i>could possibly break</i>

38:51.913 --> 38:54.958
<i>which then has me worried that</i>
<i>I really screwed something up.</i>

38:54.958 --> 38:55.753
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:02.298 --> 39:04.425
- It ain't critical.

39:04.425 --> 39:06.177
<i>- Just like that one broke,</i>

39:06.177 --> 39:08.179
<i>any of the other ones</i>
<i>could possibly break,</i>

39:08.179 --> 39:11.724
<i>which then has me worried that</i>
<i>I really screwed something up.</i>

39:11.724 --> 39:14.727
<i>[tense music]</i>

39:14.727 --> 39:21.860
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:24.821 --> 39:27.615
- First up, it's obvious.

39:27.615 --> 39:29.534
The problem here
is you lost a blade.

39:29.534 --> 39:32.245
With the welds that
you have here, it broke.

39:32.245 --> 39:34.998
That's why
you have other blades

39:34.998 --> 39:36.708
to help out with the fight.

39:36.708 --> 39:38.334
Your blades are wicked sharp.

39:38.334 --> 39:40.003
Because they're
so much lighter,

39:40.003 --> 39:42.463
the cuts
are deeper and sharper.

39:42.463 --> 39:44.632
Because your damage
is not catastrophic...

39:44.632 --> 39:45.842
it will kill.

39:47.760 --> 39:50.179
Next up, the strength test.

39:50.179 --> 39:51.598
Dave.

39:51.598 --> 39:54.976
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:54.976 --> 39:57.145
- Now, to test the strength
and overall construction

39:57.145 --> 39:58.605
of your wind and fire rings,

39:58.605 --> 40:01.524
I'll be attacking
our bamboo Wushu dummy.

40:01.524 --> 40:03.192
Rebel, you're up first.
You ready?

40:03.192 --> 40:05.028
- Definitely.
- All right.

40:05.028 --> 40:08.031
<i>[tense music]</i>

40:08.031 --> 40:14.662
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:16.414 --> 40:19.417
<i>[heavy metal music]</i>

40:19.417 --> 40:26.007
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:27.300 --> 40:29.802
- Damn.

40:29.802 --> 40:34.015
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:34.015 --> 40:37.101
- Okay, so right off, Rebel,
those points are wicked.

40:37.101 --> 40:39.479
They are nice
and sharp and strong.

40:39.479 --> 40:42.231
There's a lot of weight
to these blades,

40:42.231 --> 40:44.442
but I think
your construction technique

40:44.442 --> 40:45.860
is brilliant.
Nicely done.

40:45.860 --> 40:47.195
- Thank you.

40:47.195 --> 40:49.530
- All right, Chuck, you ready?
- Yep.

40:49.530 --> 40:51.950
- Okay.

40:51.950 --> 40:59.040
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:09.717 --> 41:13.638
So, Chuck,
we lost another one.

41:13.638 --> 41:15.181
They feel good.

41:15.181 --> 41:17.016
They're light, they're fast,
they're sharp...

41:17.016 --> 41:19.435
but they're coming apart.

41:19.435 --> 41:22.230
So, Chuck, the bottom line is,
with this kind of damage,

41:22.230 --> 41:24.399
I can't safely continue
to test these.

41:24.399 --> 41:26.401
- I understand.
- All right.

41:26.401 --> 41:29.112
- Chuck, now we have
a vote of no confidence

41:29.112 --> 41:32.448
from the judges to move forward
in this testing,

41:32.448 --> 41:34.450
and for that reason
I have to ask you

41:34.450 --> 41:37.161
to please leave The Forge.

41:37.161 --> 41:38.871
- Thanks for putting up
a good fight.

41:38.871 --> 41:40.164
- No problem.

41:40.164 --> 41:42.041
<i>I don't mind losing to Rebel.</i>

41:42.041 --> 41:44.460
He came up with
a brilliant design.

41:44.460 --> 41:46.629
<i>I may not have won,</i>
<i>but I always figured</i>

41:46.629 --> 41:49.090
<i>if I could get a good</i>
<i>"it'll kill" out of Doug,</i>

41:49.090 --> 41:50.550
I won.

41:50.550 --> 41:53.219
And I did and I'm
pretty excited about that.

41:53.219 --> 41:54.721
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:54.721 --> 41:56.389
- Well, Rebel...

41:56.389 --> 41:58.683
this is a competition
where the best blade wins,

41:58.683 --> 42:01.269
and your pair
of apocalypse rings

42:01.269 --> 42:03.104
have definitely put you on top.

42:03.104 --> 42:06.065
Congratulations, you are our
new "Forged in Fire" champion,

42:06.065 --> 42:08.860
and that's a title that comes
with a check for $10,000.

42:08.860 --> 42:12.238
Good job, brother.
[applause]

42:12.238 --> 42:14.407
<i>- I am</i>
<i>a "Forged in Fire" champion</i>

42:14.407 --> 42:16.200
<i>and it feels really great.</i>

42:16.200 --> 42:18.953
Although, I'm very proud of
Chuck for pushing through it

42:18.953 --> 42:21.330
and being a real fighter,
I didn't want to win like this,

42:21.330 --> 42:24.125
but I've learned that
with a little ingenuity

42:24.125 --> 42:26.586
and a little crazy
you can turn the impossible

42:26.586 --> 42:29.255
into the possible
and totally win this.

42:29.255 --> 42:34.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

